    "content": {
      "language": "en",
      "problem_latex": "Jenny need to reach her teacher house by $$2.15 \\rm{p.m}$$ for piano class. From her house to teacher\\textquotesingle s house, she need to walk for $$20$$ minutes. She was late for $$10$$ minutes. What time did she leave her house?\n(A) 2.05 \\rm{a.m.}\n(B) 2.05 \\rm{p.m.}\n(C) 1.55 \\rm{a.m.}\n(D) 1.55 \\rm{p.m.}\n(E) 2.25 \\rm{p.m.}",
      "problem_plain": "Jenny need to reach her teacher house by 2.15 p.m for piano class. From her house to teacher s house, she need to walk for 20 minutes. She was late for 10 minutes. What time did she leave her house? (A) 2.05 a.m. (B) 2.05 p.m. (C) 1.55 a.m. (D) 1.55 p.m. (E) 2.25 p.m.",
      "solution_latex": "She reached at $$2.25 \\rm{p.m.}$$, thus, $$20$$ minutes before that is $$2.05 \\rm{p.m.}$$",
      "solution_plain": "She reached at 2.25 p.m. , thus, 20 minutes before that is 2.05 p.m."
